text.tspan: Access to electricity vs. GDP per capita, 1990 to 2020
Access to electricity is defined here as having enough power for basic lighting and charging a phone for 4 hours.
GDP per capita is adjusted for inflation and differences in the cost of living between countries.
Data source: Data compiled from multiple sources by World Bank
Note: GDP per capita is expressed in international-$ at 2017 prices.
